<TITLE> 3 killed, 4 hurt in 2 accidents </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, May 13 (bdnews24.com)  Three persons were killed and at least four were injured in two accidents at Savar and Ashulia. The injured were admitted to local hospitals. The accidents occurred at Sripur of Ashulia and Thana bus stand of Savar. Golam Mostafa Chowdhury, a sub inspector of Ashulia said that a truck lost control as it tried to make space for a Dhaka-bound bus and hit passers-by at Sripur bus stand of Ashulia on Thursday morning at around 10am. Two died on the spot and four were injured. One of the bodies was identified as that of Harun-Ur-Rashid (25). Police captured the truck and the bus, but the drivers escaped the scene. In the other accident, Savar sub inspector Saiful Islam said that a speeding bus crushed a woman, Fatema (40), while she was crossing the road. Locals seized the bus but the driver escaped. The bodies were taken to police station. Cases were filed with Savar and Ashulia police stations. b
